The article extends warm wishes to Muslims celebrating Eid al-Fitr, marking the end of Ramadan. It highlights the importance of coming together as families and communities to celebrate blessings and reflect on devotion. It also emphasizes the need to remember those who are struggling and to work towards a better future. The article expresses solidarity with displaced persons and refugees who are separated from their families. It calls for the nation to uphold its commitment to serving as a beacon of hope for oppressed people. The article also emphasizes the importance of respecting all faiths and beliefs, as urged by the Holy Qur'an. It mentions the tradition of celebrating Eid at the White House and honoring Muslim Americans who promote understanding and unity. The article concludes by wishing a Happy Eid and hoping for the spirit of community, compassion, and service to continue throughout the year.